This paper is about the evaluation of a semantic representation language, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with machine learning algorithms and evaluation metrics, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different parsers, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
